[{"id":31684,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Solutions","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"$\\begin{aligned}\n& \\mathrm{HX} \\rightleftharpoons \\mathrm{H}^{+}+\\mathrm{X}^{-} \\quad \\mathrm{K}_{\\mathrm{a}}=1.2 \\times 10^{-5} \\\\\n& 0.03 \\mathrm{M} \\\\\n& 0.03-\\mathrm{x} \\quad \\mathrm{x} \\quad \\mathrm{x} \\\\\n& \\mathrm{K}_{\\mathrm{a}}=1.2 \\times 10^{-5}=\\frac{\\mathrm{x}^2}{0.03-\\mathrm{x}} \\\\\n& 0.03-\\mathrm{x} \\approx 0.03\\left(\\mathrm{~K}_{\\mathrm{a}} \\text { is very small }\\right) \\\\\n& \\frac{\\mathrm{x}^2}{0.03}=1.2 \\times 10^{-5} \\\\\n& \\mathrm{x}=6 \\times 10^{-4}\n\\end{aligned}$<br />Final solution : $0.03-x+x+x$\n$\\begin{aligned}\n& =0.03+x=0.03+6 \\times 10^{-4} \\\\\n& \\Pi=\\left(0.03+\\left(6 \\times 10^{-4}\\right)\\right) \\times 0.083 \\times 300 \\\\\n& =76.19 \\times 10^{-2} \\approx 76 \\times 10^{-2}\n\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (06 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31640,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Solutions","question":"","options":["Both Statement I and Statement II are true","Both Statement I and Statement II are false","Statement I is true but Statement II is false","Statement I is false but Statement II is true"],"answer":3,"solution":"Statement I: $1,2,3$-Trihydroxypropane (glycerol) has a very high boiling point (around $290^{\\circ}\\text{C}$) and it decomposes at its boiling point under normal atmospheric pressure. Therefore, it cannot be separated from water by simple distillation. Instead, it is separated by distillation under reduced pressure (vacuum distillation). Hence, Statement I is false.<br><br>Statement II: An azeotropic mixture is a constant boiling mixture in which the liquid and vapour phases have the exact same composition. Because there is no change in composition upon boiling, the components of an azeotropic mixture cannot be separated by fractional distillation. Hence, Statement II is true.<br><br>Therefore, Statement I is false but Statement II is true.<br><br>Answer: Statement I is false but Statement II is true","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (02 April Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31775,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Solutions","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Given <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msubsup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mn>0</mn></msubsup><mo>=</mo><mn>21</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kPa</mi><mo>&#160;&#160;</mo><mo>&#8658;</mo><msubsup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mn>0</mn></msubsup><mo>=</mo><mn>18</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kPa</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8594;</mo></math> An Ideal solution is prepared by mixing <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp;mole <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn></math> mole <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math>.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8594;</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8594;</mo></math> According to Raoult&#39;s law</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></msub><msubsup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mn>0</mn></msubsup><mo>+</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></msub><msubsup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mn>0</mn></msubsup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mo>&#160;&#160;</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>21</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>18</mn></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mo>&#160;&#160;</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>12</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>19</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kPa</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (16 Mar Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":31789,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Solutions","question":"","options":["Osmosis","Dialysis","Diffusion","Reverse osmosis"],"answer":0,"solution":"When mango kept in concentrate salt solution then solvent (water) flow from mango to concentrate solution that&#39;s why mango shrinks this is called. &quot;Osmosis&quot;","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (02 Sep Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":31778,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Solutions","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Sol <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable columnalign=\"center center left left\"><mtr><mtd><msub><mi>SO</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mtd><mtd><mo>+</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>2</mn><mi>NaOH</mi></mtd><mtd><mo>&#8594;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi>Na</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>SO</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></mtd><mtd><mo>+</mo></mtd><mtd><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mfrac><mn>224</mn><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0821</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>298</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mol</mi></mtd><mtd></mtd><mtd><mn>10</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mmol</mi></mtd><mtd></mtd><mtd><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mmol</mi></mtd><mtd></mtd><mtd></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">L</mi><mo>.</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi><mo>.</mo><mo>)</mo></mtd><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>)</mo></mtd><mtd></mtd><mtd></mtd></mtr></mtable></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mn>0</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></msup><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>iX</mi><mrow><mi>solute</mi><mo>&#160;</mo></mrow></msub><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mn>0</mn></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>24</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>18</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>18</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp;mm of Hg</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (26 Feb Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31675,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Solutions","question":"","options":["$\\frac{\\mathrm{P}_2^0}{\\mathrm{P}_1^0}, \\frac{\\mathrm{P}_2^0-\\mathrm{P}_1^0}{\\mathrm{P}_2^0}$","$\\frac{\\mathrm{P}_1^0}{\\mathrm{P}_2^0}, \\frac{\\mathrm{P}_2^0-\\mathrm{P}_1^0}{\\mathrm{P}_2^0}$","$\\frac{\\mathrm{P}_1^0}{\\mathrm{P}_2^0}, \\frac{\\mathrm{P}_1^0-\\mathrm{P}_2^0}{\\mathrm{P}_2^0}$","$\\frac{\\mathrm{P}_2^0}{\\mathrm{P}_1^0}, \\frac{\\mathrm{P}_1^0-\\mathrm{P}_2^0}{\\mathrm{P}_2^0}$"],"answer":1,"solution":"Given mole fraction of liquid 1 in liquid and vapour phase is $x_1$ and $y_1$ respectively.\n<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ZYP2Z_DjqkV7FiPFkgzqA4OCvPDI1s6oCdNvcRnoAms.original.fullsize.png\"><br>\n\n$\\begin{aligned} & \\mathrm{P}_1=\\mathrm{P}_{\\mathrm{T}} y_1=\\mathrm{P}_1^0 x_1 \\\\ & \\frac{\\mathrm{P}_{\\mathrm{T}}}{x_1}=\\frac{\\mathrm{P}_1^0}{y_1} \\\\ & \\frac{\\mathrm{P}_2^0+x_1\\left(\\mathrm{P}_1^0+\\mathrm{P}_2^0\\right)}{x_1}=\\frac{\\mathrm{P}_1^0}{y_1} \\\\ & \\frac{\\mathrm{P}_2^0}{x_1}+\\left(\\mathrm{P}_1^0+\\mathrm{P}_2^0\\right)=\\frac{\\mathrm{P}_1^0}{y_1} \\\\ & \\frac{\\mathrm{P}_2^0}{x_1}=\\frac{\\mathrm{P}_1^0}{y_1}-\\left(\\mathrm{P}_1^0+\\mathrm{P}_2^0\\right) \\\\ & \\frac{1}{x_1}=\\frac{1}{y_2}\\left(\\frac{\\mathrm{P}_1^0}{\\mathrm{P}_2^0}\\right)-\\frac{\\left(\\mathrm{P}_1^0+\\mathrm{P}_2^0\\right)}{\\mathrm{P}_2^0}\\end{aligned}$\n$\\begin{aligned} & \\frac{1}{x_1}=\\frac{1}{y_2}\\left(\\frac{P_1^0}{P_2^0}\\right)+\\frac{\\left(P_2^0-P_1^0\\right)}{P_2^0} \\\\ & y=m x+c \\\\ & \\text { Slope }=\\frac{P_1^0}{P_2^0} ; \\text { Intercept }=\\frac{P_2^0-P_1^0}{P_2^0}\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (23 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":31777,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Solutions","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>&#916;T</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">f</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">f</mi></msub><mo>&#215;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>93</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>86</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>12</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>122</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>100</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>1000</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>93</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>86</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#945;</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (26 Feb Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":31816,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Solutions","question":"","options":["$\\frac{3}{4}$","$\\frac{1}{2}$","$\\frac{1}{4}$","$\\frac{4}{3}$"],"answer":0,"solution":"The relationship between molar masses of the two solvents is\n$$\n\\mathrm{M}_{\\mathrm{X}}=\\frac{3}{4} \\mathrm{M}_{\\mathrm{Y}}\n$$\nThe relative lowering of vapour pressure of the two solutions is\n$$\n\\left(\\frac{\\Delta \\mathrm{P}}{\\mathrm{P}}\\right)_{\\mathrm{X}}=\\mathrm{m}\\left(\\frac{\\Delta \\mathrm{P}}{\\mathrm{P}}\\right)_{\\mathrm{Y}}\n$$\nBut, the relative lowering of vapour pressure of solutions is directly proportional to the mole fraction of solute.\nGiven 5 molal solution, means 5 moles of solute are dissolved in $1 \\mathrm{~kg}$ ( or $1000 \\mathrm{~g}$ ) of solvent.\nThe number of moles of solvent $=\\frac{1000 \\mathrm{~g}}{\\mathrm{M}}$\nThe mole fraction of solute $=\\frac{5}{1000 / \\mathrm{M}}$\n$$\n=\\mathrm{M} \\times \\frac{5}{1000}\n$$\nhence $\\mathrm{M}_{\\mathrm{X}} \\times \\frac{5}{1000}=\\mathrm{m} \\times \\mathrm{M}_{\\mathrm{Y}} \\times \\frac{5}{1000}$.\nSubstitute equation (i) in equation (ii)\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n&\\frac{3}{4} \\times \\mathrm{M}_{\\mathrm{Y}} \\times \\frac{5}{1000}=\\mathrm{m} \\times \\mathrm{M}_{\\mathrm{Y}} \\times \\frac{5}{1000} \\\\\n&\\mathrm{~m}=\\frac{3}{4}\n\\end{aligned}\n$$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2018 (15 Apr Shift 2 Online)","image":null},{"id":31838,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Solutions","question":"","options":["400","1000","250","200"],"answer":0,"solution":"$\\begin{aligned} \\text { ppm } & =\\frac{\\text { wt. of solute }}{\\text { wt. of solvent }} \\times 10^6 \\\\ & =\\frac{0.2}{500} \\times 10^6=400\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2012 (12 May Online)","image":null},{"id":31811,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Solutions","question":"","options":["<math><msub><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0.4</mn><mo>;</mo><msub><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0.6</mn></math>","<math><msub><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0.76</mn><mo>;</mo><msub><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0.24</mn></math>","<math><msub><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0.28</mn><mo>;</mo><msub><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0.72</mn></math>","<math><msub><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0.37</mn><mo>;</mo><msub><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0.63</mn></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"Since, <math><msubsup><mrow><mi>P</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msubsup><mo>=</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><mi>P</mi><mi>a</mi><mo>;</mo><mtext> </mtext><msubsup><mrow><mi>P</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msubsup><mo>=</mo><mn>12</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><mi>P</mi><mi>a</mi></math> and <math><msub><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0.4</mn></math>,&nbsp;<math> <mrow> <msub> <mi>X</mi> <mi>B</mi> </msub> <mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>−</mo><mn>0.4</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0.6</mn></mrow> </math><br /><br />According to Raoult's Law: <math><msub><mrow><mi>P</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><msubsup><mrow><mi>P</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msubsup><msub><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></msub><mo>+</mo><msubsup><mrow><mi>P</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msubsup><msub><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></msub></math><br /><br /><math><msub><mrow><mi>P</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>7</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>0.4</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>12</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>0.6</mn></mrow></mfenced></math><br /><br /><math><msub><mrow><mi>P</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><mi>P</mi><mi>a</mi></math><br /><br />Now, <math><msubsup><mrow><mi>P</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msubsup><msub><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mrow><mi>P</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></msub></math><br /><br /><math><msub><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msubsup><mrow><mi>P</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msubsup><msub><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>P</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>7</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><mo>×</mo><mn>0.4</mn></mrow><mrow><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>⇒</mo><mn>0.28</mn></math><br /><br /><math><msub><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><msub><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></msub><mo>⇒</mo><mtext> </mtext><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>0.28</mn><mo>⇒</mo><mn>0.72</mn></math><br /><br />&nbsp;","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (10 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31801,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Solutions","question":"","options":["<math><mn>4</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math><mn>16</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math><mn>4</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math><mn>6</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p>Osmotic pressure <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#960;</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></math></p><p><math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>=</mo></math>Van&#39;t&nbsp;hoff factor</p><p>According to question,</p><p>for XY&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi><mn>2</mn></msu