tp://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4000</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></msub><mrow><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mtext>water&#160;</mtext></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mi>water</mi></msub></mfrac></math></p><p>Means <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math> mole water <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>18</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>gm</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>18</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>ml</mi></mrow></mfenced></math> dissolves</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4000</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;moles&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>.</mo></math>&nbsp;Hence, molar solubility</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4000</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mn>18</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>1000</mn><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>72</mn></mfrac><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mol</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi>dm</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>1388</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>89</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mol</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi>dm</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#8776;</mo><mn>1389</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mol</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi>dm</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (17 Mar Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31681,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Solutions","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"$\\begin{aligned} & \\mathrm{AB}_2 \\rightarrow \\mathrm{A}^{+2}+2 \\mathrm{~B}^{\\ominus} \\\\ & \\mathrm{i}=1+(3-1) \\alpha \\\\ & \\mathrm{i}=1+2 \\alpha \\\\ & \\Delta \\mathrm{T}_{\\mathrm{b}}=\\mathrm{k}_{\\mathrm{b}} \\mathrm{im} \\\\ & 0.52=0.52(1+2 \\alpha) \\frac{\\frac{10}{200}}{\\frac{100}{1000}} \\\\ & 1=(1+2 \\alpha) \\frac{10}{20} \\\\ & 2=1+2 \\alpha \\\\ & \\alpha=0.5\\end{aligned}$\nAns. $\\alpha=5 \\times 10^{-1}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (08 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31843,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Solutions","question":"","options":["$0.0372 \\mathrm{~K}$","$0.0558 \\mathrm{~K}$","$0.0744 \\mathrm{~K}$","$0.0186 \\mathrm{~K}$"],"answer":1,"solution":"Vant Hoff's factor (i) for $\\mathrm{Na}_2 \\mathrm{SO}_4=3$\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n\\therefore \\Delta \\mathrm{T}_{\\mathrm{f}}= & \\text { (i) } \\mathrm{k}_{\\mathrm{f}} \\mathrm{m} \\\\\n& =3 \\times 1.80 \\times \\frac{0.01}{1}=0.0558 \\mathrm{~K}\n\\end{aligned}\n$$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2010","image":null},{"id":31663,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Solutions","question":"","options":["379.2 K","377.3 K","375.3 K","277.3 K"],"answer":1,"solution":"$\\begin{aligned} & \\Delta \\mathrm{T}_{\\mathrm{b}}=\\mathrm{i}_1 \\mathrm{~m}_1 \\mathrm{k}_{\\mathrm{b}}+\\mathrm{i}_2 \\mathrm{~m}_2 \\mathrm{k}_{\\mathrm{b}} \\\\ & =1 \\times \\frac{2}{0.5} \\times 0.52+\\frac{1 \\times 2}{0.5} \\times 0.52=4.16 \\\\ & \\left(\\mathrm{~T}_{\\mathrm{b}}\\right)_{\\text {solution }}=373.16+4.16=377.3 \\mathrm{~K}.\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (3 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31680,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Solutions","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"Molality of urea is $4.44 \\mathrm{~m}$, that means 4.44 moles of urea present in $1000 \\mathrm{gm}$ of water.\n$\\therefore \\mathrm{X}_{\\text {ura }}=\\frac{4.44}{4.44+\\frac{1000}{18}}$\n$=0.0740$\nOR\n$\\begin{aligned} & 74 \\times 10^{-3} \\\\ & X=74\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (08 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":31837,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Solutions","question":"","options":["$1.36 \\%$","$73.5 \\%$","$7.35 \\%$","$2.47 \\%$"],"answer":1,"solution":"$$\n\\text { Mol.wt. }=\\frac{k_f \\times w \\times 1000}{\\Delta T_f \\times W}=\\frac{1.86 \\times 0.85 \\times 1000}{0.23 \\times 125} \\approx 55 \\mathrm{gm}\n$$\nWhere\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n& w=0.85 \\mathrm{~g} \\\\\n& W=125 \\mathrm{~g} \\\\\n& \\Delta T_f=0^{\\circ} \\mathrm{C}-\\left(-23^{\\circ} \\mathrm{C}\\right)=23^{\\circ} \\mathrm{C}\n\\end{aligned}\n$$\nNow, $i=\\frac{M_{\\text {normal }}}{M_{\\text {observed }}}=\\frac{136.3}{55}=2.47$\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n& \\underset{1-\\alpha}{\\mathrm{ZnCl}_2} \\leftrightharpoons \\underset{\\alpha}{\\mathrm{Zn}^{++}}+\\underset{2 \\alpha}{2 \\mathrm{Cl}^{-}} \\\\\n& \\text {Van't Hoff factor ( } i \\text { ) } \\\\\n& =\\frac{1-\\alpha+\\alpha+2 \\alpha}{1}=2.47 \\\\\n& \\therefore \\quad \\alpha=0.735=73.5 \\% \\\\\n&\n\\end{aligned}\n$$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2012 (12 May Online)","image":null},{"id":31819,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Solutions","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>25</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>65</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>15</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>45</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>Na</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>SO</mi><mn>4</mn></msub><mo>&#8594;</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>Na</mi><mo>+</mo></msup><mo>+</mo><msubsup><mi>SO</mi><mn>4</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo></mrow></msubsup></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mn>0</mn><mo>.815</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.63</mo></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>.82</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.86</mo><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.63</mo><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>1000</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>142</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8756;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.86</mo><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.63</mo><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>5000</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>142</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>.82</mo></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>45</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mi>gm</mi></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2017 (08 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":31660,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Solutions","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"Sea water is 6 Molar in NaCl , So 1000 ml of sea water contains 6 mol of NaCl.<br />mass of solution $=$ Volume $\\times$ density<br />$=1000 \\times 2$<br />mass of solution $=2000 \\mathrm{~g}$<br />$\\begin{aligned}<br />& \\text { ppm }=\\frac{\\text { mass of } \\mathrm{O}_2}{2000} \\times 10^6 \\\\<br>& \\text { mass of } \\mathrm{O}_2=5.8 \\times 2 \\times 10^{-3} \\\\<br>& \\quad=1.16 \\times 10^{-2} \\mathrm{~g}<br />\\end{aligned}$<br />molality for $\\mathrm{O}_2=\\frac{1.16 \\times 10^{-2} / 32}{(2000-6 \\times 58.5)} \\times 1000$<br />$\\begin{aligne